---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import ArticleLayout from '../../components/ArticleLayout.astro';
import Toc from '../../components/Toc.astro';
import ArticleHero from '../../components/ArticleHero.astro';
import ImagePair from '../../components/ImagePair.astro';
import ImageTrio from '../../components/ImageTrio.astro';
import '../../styles/article.css';
---

<BaseLayout title="Studio Pepper — Jessica Suh">
  <Header />
  <main class="highlight-page">
    <ArticleHero
      title="Brands: Studio Pepper"
      logoSrc="/images/studio-pepper/pepper-logo.png"
      logoAlt="Studio Pepper"
      logoWidth="80px"
      imageSrc="/images/studio-pepper/nft-prereveal.gif"
      imageAlt="Studio Pepper PeppiCar"
    />

    <!-- Article: TOC + Content -->
    <ArticleLayout>
      <Toc
        slot="toc"
        items={[
          { label: "A different kind of Creative Space", href: "#creative-space" },
          { label: "The Origin", href: "#origin" },
          { label: "The Characters", href: "#characters" },
          { label: "The Cars", href: "#cars" },
          { label: "Meet Their Drivers", href: "#meet-drivers" },
          { label: "What's Coming", href: "#whats-coming" },
          { label: "The Team", href: "#team" },
        ]}
        paddingTop="286px"
      />
      <div class="content">
        <!-- Intro -->
        <div class="intro">
          <p class="subtitle" style="text-align: center;">
            <span class="subtitle-heading">Just spiced up enough to make you smile.</span><br />
            <span class="subtitle-description">A character IP studio built where everything begins.</span>
          </p>
          <div class="divider-full"></div>
          <p class="nda">
            This is a personal side project, entirely my own universe. No NDAs here.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- A different kind of creative space -->
        <section id="creative-space">
          <h2>A different kind of creative space</h2>
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>Professional automotive design runs on constraints (regulations, packaging, engineering sign-off etc&hellip;) Those constraints are what make the work rigorous, and I love them for it. But every designer needs a place to breathe. Studio Pepper was built as the opposite of that, a creative space where the only brief is expression.</p>
            <p>The name comes from a single cheeky twist on the racing flag. Same DNA, different flavor. That logic runs through everything: the characters, the vehicles, the universe. It all starts from automotive thinking.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <div class="divider-full"></div>

        <!-- The Origin -->
        <section id="origin">
          <p class="section-tag">The Origin</p>
          <h2>A different kind of creative space</h2>
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>COVID gave everyone too much time and not enough to do with it. I was stuck in a loop of playing KartRider Rush every day and cooking more than I ever had before.</p>
            <p>Then one evening, I was grinding pepper when the lid just snapped off. Peppercorns scattered everywhere. As I was picking them up one by one, I started looking at them differently.</p>
            <p>Like, what if they think I&rsquo;m some Evil Chef? To them, I&rsquo;m this giant villain, and they&rsquo;re all just trying to run for their lives. I realized it was actually a cool game idea, and that maybe I should be building them instead of just playing KartRider. I started by sketching that concept out: an &ldquo;Evil Chef&rdquo; trying to grind them while they scramble to escape before they get shattered.</p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/studio-pepper/game-sketch.png" alt="Initial game idea sketch" class="section-image" />
          <p class="image-caption">My initial game idea sketch</p>
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>After that, my KartRider brain kicked in: They need a car. They need to get away from the evil me 😈😈😈.</p>
            <p>From there, the ideas just exploded. I realized not everything had to be &ldquo;car-shaped.&rdquo; Why not an ice cream bar with wheels? Or a sofa with wheels? Whatever they could find to escape! I put together a collage of all these wild vehicle concepts, and my friends loved it. That was the moment we decided to take it seriously and actually make something out of it.</p>
          </div>
          <ImagePair>
            <img src="/images/studio-pepper/car-collage-01.png" alt="Pepper car idea collage" />
            <img src="/images/studio-pepper/car-collage-02.png" alt="Pepper car idea collage" />
          </ImagePair>
          <p class="image-caption">My initial pepper car idea collage</p>
        </section>

        <div class="divider-full"></div>

        <!-- The Characters -->
        <section id="characters">
          <p class="section-tag">The Characters</p>
          <h2>The PEPPERCORNS !</h2>
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>When my friends told me they wanted to join the project, I started to characterize them. Characterizing my friends as little pepper grains after a long day of fighting rigid engineering tolerances was the most relief I&rsquo;d felt in months.</p>
            <p>I told them to name themselves after their favorite celebrities (you can probably guess who they are by their first names, but I&rsquo;m not telling!) These five original characters each carry a distinct personality, a distinct flavor, and enough range to go anywhere. I started with manual sketches and then built them into Blender (back then, there was no AI; this was all me).</p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/studio-pepper/peppi-collection.png" alt="Initial peppi sketch" class="section-image" />
          <p class="image-caption">Initial peppi sketch</p>
          <ImageTrio>
            <img src="/images/studio-pepper/blender-render-01.png" alt="Blender Peppi rendering" />
            <img src="/images/studio-pepper/blender-render-02.png" alt="Blender Peppi rendering" />
            <img src="/images/studio-pepper/blender-render-03.png" alt="Hades Leo preview" />
          </ImageTrio>
          <p class="image-caption">Preview Blender Peppi Renderings</p>
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>Pepper tastes best freshly ground. So we&rsquo;re staying whole.<br />Until we&rsquo;re ready to be served on our own terms. Here we are:</p>
          </div>

          <div class="character-grid">
            <div class="character-item">
              <img src="/images/studio-pepper/peppi-gigi.png" alt="Gigi the Polarizer" />
              <p class="character-name">1. Gigi the Polarizer</p>
              <p>tastes like spicy cherry. Go hard or go home. She wants to be the most savory pepper grain in the world.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="character-item">
              <img src="/images/studio-pepper/peppi-tom.png" alt="Tom the Bipolar" />
              <p class="character-name">2. Tom the Bipolar</p>
              <p>tastes like spicy rainbow sherbet. His personality shifts with every environment. Proceed with caution.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="character-item">
              <img src="/images/studio-pepper/peppi-brad.png" alt="Brad the Rule Breaker" />
              <p class="character-name">3. Brad the Rule Breaker</p>
              <p>tastes like spicy cinnamon banana. Mischievous to the core, chasing dopamine and fun every single day.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="character-item">
              <img src="/images/studio-pepper/peppi-rachel.png" alt="Rachel the Socialite" />
              <p class="character-name">4. Rachel the Socialite</p>
              <p>tastes like spicy rose. The moment you meet her, you&rsquo;re already in her circle. She&rsquo;s taking you everywhere worth being and you didn&rsquo;t even ask to come.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="character-item">
              <img src="/images/studio-pepper/peppi-leo.png" alt="Leo the Nature Lover" />
              <p class="character-name">5. Leo the Nature Lover</p>
              <p>tastes like spicy fresh basil mint. Mindful, sustainable, and someday he just wants to disappear back into nature entirely.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <img src="/images/studio-pepper/pepper-animation.gif" alt="Pepper character animation" class="section-image" />

          <h2>The 8888 Peppis</h2>
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>Then we decided to turn it into an NFT project to see where it could go.</p>
            <p>So, for ONE FULL YEAR, we worked together to build a collection of 8,888 of them. The collection runs all five Peppis through wildly different themes. Everything from Greek gods and snack editions to seasonal versions. Each one was designed by hand; no two are the same.</p>
          </div>
          <ImagePair>
            <img src="/images/studio-pepper/pepper-collection-01.png" alt="Pepper collection" />
            <img src="/images/studio-pepper/pepper-collection-02.png" alt="Pepper collection" />
          </ImagePair>


        </section>

        <div class="divider-full"></div>

        <!-- The Cars -->
        <section id="cars">
          <p class="section-tag">The Cars</p>
          <h2>Automotive design thinking turned inside out</h2>
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>Forget everything you know about how a car is supposed to look. The Peppi Car starts from a single truth: pepper is round. So the wheels are round. Not just round, they are full spheres, made from actual pepper grains, and they roll in any direction because that is what spheres do.</p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/studio-pepper/car-design-01.png" alt="PeppiCar design" class="section-image" />
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>Every Peppi Car is built on the same platform, six components shared across the entire lineup:</p>
          </div>
          <ImagePair>
            <img src="/images/studio-pepper/car-component-01.png" alt="PeppiCar components" />
            <img src="/images/studio-pepper/car-component-02.png" alt="PeppiCar components" />
          </ImagePair>
          <div class="two-column-grid">
            <div class="column">
              <p><strong>Body Cover.</strong> The design skin. Where each car&rsquo;s personality lives. Same platform underneath, completely different attitude on top.</p>
              <p><strong>Wheel Cover.</strong> A donut-shaped ring that wraps around each sphere pepper tires like a &ldquo;My Precious.&rdquo;</p>
              <p><strong>Sphere Wheels.</strong> Pure pepper. The signature of the entire Peppi Car universe. They go everywhere.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="column">
              <p><strong>Peppi Bed.</strong> The softest cushion in the entire world. This is where the Peppi sits. Once they&rsquo;re in, they&rsquo;re one. If you are Salt or Sugar, you can&rsquo;t sit here.</p>
              <p><strong>Hyper Booster.</strong> Because what is a pepper grain without a kick. Mounted for maximum acceleration. Handle with care.</p>
              <p><strong>Battery Pack.</strong> Four special packs mounted at the sides. The pepper world runs on its own energy and it runs hot.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <ImagePair>
            <img src="/images/studio-pepper/car-component-03.png" alt="PeppiCar components" />
            <img src="/images/studio-pepper/car-component-04.png" alt="PeppiCar components" />
          </ImagePair>

          <h2>The Five Cars</h2>
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>The Racer, The GTS, The Donut, The Teeth and The Nature.</p>
            <p>Every car has a Peppi. Every Peppi has a car. Personality-matched, inseparable, and together they form a complete collectible set.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="car-grid">
            <div class="car-item">
              <img src="/images/studio-pepper/car-racer.png" alt="The Racer" />
              <p class="car-name">1. The Racer.</p>
              <p>Pure, uncompromising. Built for one thing and one thing only.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="car-item">
              <img src="/images/studio-pepper/car-gts.png" alt="The GTS" />
              <p class="car-name">2. The GTS.</p>
              <p>The Racer&rsquo;s more refined sibling. The kind of car that wins without looking like it was trying.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="car-item">
              <img src="/images/studio-pepper/car-donut.png" alt="The Donut" />
              <p class="car-name">3. The Donut.</p>
              <p>Not going anywhere in a straight line and doesn&rsquo;t want to. Built for yumminess, spinning, circling, showing up and being seen.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="car-item">
              <img src="/images/studio-pepper/car-teeth.png" alt="The Teeth" />
              <p class="car-name">4. The Teeth.</p>
              <p>Chaotic where the GTS is composed. This one isn&rsquo;t hiding anything. It looks for trouble and finds it every single time. The bodywork says threat before the engine even starts.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="car-item">
              <img src="/images/studio-pepper/car-nature.png" alt="The Nature" />
              <p class="car-name">5. The Nature.</p>
              <p>Branches and organic materials grow directly into the bodywork. Nature isn&rsquo;t a feature here. It&rsquo;s the structure. It didn&rsquo;t choose to be sustainable. It just grew that way.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>The result looks like a kart. A very, very fancy kart. Low, no roof, no doors, just the PeppiCar, the road, and whatever chaos comes next.</p>
            <p>Peppicar also has a collection of 8,888 of them. The collection runs all five Peppicars through wildly different themes. Each one was designed by hand; no two are the same.</p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/studio-pepper/peppicar-design-02.png" alt="PeppiCar collection" class="section-image" />
        </section>

        <div class="divider-full"></div>

        <!-- Meet their drivers -->
        <section id="meet-drivers">
          <h2>Meet their drivers.</h2>
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>But the combinations don&rsquo;t have to follow the rules. Gigi in the Teeth as a Greek god edition? Absolutely. Any Peppi, any car, any theme. Mix, match, and make it yours.</p>
          </div>
          <ImagePair>
            <img src="/images/studio-pepper/photo-01.png" alt="Peppi drivers combination" />
            <img src="/images/studio-pepper/photo-02.png" alt="Peppi drivers combination" />
          </ImagePair>
        </section>

        <div class="divider-full"></div>

        <!-- What's coming -->
        <section id="whats-coming">
          <h2>What&rsquo;s coming</h2>
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>We&rsquo;re already thinking about a racing game with original track designs. A world for the Peppis and their cars to actually inhabit. I&rsquo;ve even thought about physical art toys, but who knows? It&rsquo;s a surprise!</p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/studio-pepper/peppi-game-preview.gif" alt="Pepper racing game preview" class="section-image" />
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>The long-term vision is to build a full entertainment and collectible brand across digital, physical, and interactive formats. The assets are all there: 8,888 Peppis and their Peppi-cars, a game, a track, and five distinct personalities with enough range to go anywhere.</p>
            <p>So, Let&rsquo;s build something together!</p>
            <p>Always open to collaboration. If you think we could make something together, just reach out.<br />Who knows? We could be the next Labubu.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <div class="divider-full"></div>

        <!-- The team behind the pepper -->
        <section id="team">
          <h2>The team behind the pepper</h2>
          <p class="credits">To Sol You, my idea partner, for every wild &ldquo;what if&rdquo; that became the backbone of this universe. To Euno Kim, for bringing the Peppi Cars to life with real care. To Eunju Lee, for the NFT business strategy that gave the collection a framework worth believing in. And to Daniel Ryu, for building the full deployment infrastructure for all 8,888 pieces and trying on making that game&hellip;</p>
          <p class="body-text">The technical work is done. We&rsquo;re just deciding how to serve the pepper.</p>
          <ImagePair>
            <img src="/images/studio-pepper/physical-toy-01.png" alt="Studio Pepper physical toys" />
            <img src="/images/studio-pepper/physical-toy-02.png" alt="Studio Pepper physical toys" />
          </ImagePair>
          <p class="pull-quote">Fresh ground only.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </ArticleLayout>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .section-tag {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #9D9D9D;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .image-caption {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-style: italic;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: -16px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .character-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    gap: 16px;
    margin: 24px 0;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.219;
  }

  .character-grid img {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    object-fit: contain;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .character-name {
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .car-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    gap: 16px;
    margin: 24px 0;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.219;
  }

  .car-grid img {
    width: 100%;
    object-fit: contain;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .car-name {
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .pull-quote {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .credits {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: normal;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1023px) {
    .character-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
    .car-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
    .section-tag {
      font-size: 18px;
    }
    .car-name {
      font-size: 18px;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .character-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      font-size: 12px;
    }
    .character-name {
      font-size: 18px;
    }
    .car-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      font-size: 12px;
    }
    .section-tag {
      font-size: 16px;
    }
    .image-caption {
      font-size: 14px;
    }
    .car-name {
      font-size: 16px;
    }
  }
</style>
